parameters.name: レクイエム・暗い場面

parameters:
\n<Priest>"...Seriously. That guy has dumped another troublesome
matter on us."

\n<Ameria>"Asking us to 'take care of the body'... Big sis, why did
you leave this child behind?"

\n<Priest>"Who knows. She left in a hurry because she was short on
time. I'll question her when she gets back."

\n<Ameria>"...Huh? Big sis, do you know where she went? Is she coming
back soon?"

\n<Priest>"Hmm, well... I'm not sure. Since she left the body here, I
assume she'll be back soon."

\n<Priest>"...Anyway, there's no use thinking about it now. For the
time being, we'll do as she said. It's not too much trouble
to leave the body here alone."

\n<Ameria>"...Um, Pastor. About leaving it here, this is my bed, you
know."

\n<Ameria>"What do you mean 'what of it'? You're telling me to sleep
with a corpse!?"

\n<Priest>"We can't treat the deceased with disrespect. If you don't
like the floor, then pull out a bed from the storage and use
that. I'll help you move it."

\n<Ameria>"No, no, it's not about which bed... It's sleeping in the
same room that I don't like!"

\n<Priest>"Then you can sleep outside. Use the storage or the chapel,
whatever you like. We can't let the deceased sleep in a
shabby place."
\n<Ameria>"...Then, can I sleep with you, Pastor?"

\n<Priest>"If you have complaints, talk to Stella. She's the one who
brought this trouble upon us. It's only right for you, her
sister, to take care of it."

Glancing at the peacefully resting body, the priest sighed
softly.

\n<Priest>"This matter may be bigger than we think. You must take
responsibility and care for this body properly."

\n<Priest>"The body won't decay because it's been treated with
preservative magic, but make sure to wash and disinfect it
regularly. Also, wipe it down daily so it doesn't get
dusty."
\n<Priest>"...And remember to follow what Stella told you."

\n<Priest>"Someone is after this body. Never let it out of the church
and don't talk about it to anyone."

\n<Priest>"...Alright. Let's get started with washing the body. I'll
prepare everything, so you help out too."
\n<Ameria>"...I'm looking forward to working with you, Lyric."
